                        "content": "The nurse is making initial rounds on the nursing unit to check the condition of assigned clients. One client complains of discomfort at the intravenous (IV) site, and the nurse notes that the site is cool, pale, and swollen and that the solution is infusing slowly. What action would the nurse take first?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe IV must be stopped immediately because it has infiltrated. The remaining options allow the IV solution to continue to flow and further exacerbate the infiltration rather than intervene to stop it.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Integumentary\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Integumentary: Inflammation/Infection\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Tissue Integrity, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Data in the Question, Strategic Words\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, first. Then note the data in the question—discomfort at the IV site and an IV site that is cool, pale, and swollen. These signs and symptoms indicate infiltration of the IV catheter, so the first action is to stop the flow of IV solution. The nurse would then remove the IV catheter. Eliminate options 2, 3, and 4 because these actions are not aimed at stopping the problem.\n \n   ",
                        "id": "02dbcbb874114fbc8d6b56afb8d19656",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "65c2775ddc994242be834c31a1020be3",
                                "content": "Assess for drainage from the wound."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "cfad9a9264344b10a145db7fc5772408",
                                "content": "Assess for redness around the wound edges."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f84a21b4d60d44a99a72d5004e8892fc",
                                "content": "Palpate for swelling around the wound edges."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "77da00853a15490cb3f1cb5be85a1fc7",
                                "content": "Palpate for increased skin temperature around the wound edges."
                            }
                        ],
